<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idec0e157e-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70706"><num value="70706">§ 70706.</num><heading> Public meetings, information, and hearings</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idec0e157f-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70706/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Public Meetings and Release of Public Versions of Reports</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>A Commission shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1580-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70706/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> hold public hearings and meetings to the extent appropriate; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idec0e1581-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70706/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> release public versions of the reports required under this chapter.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idec0e1582-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53" identifier="/us/usc/t51/s70706/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Public Hearings</inline>.—</heading><content>Any public hearings of a Commission shall be conducted in a manner consistent with the protection of information provided to or developed for or by the Commission as required by any applicable statute, regulation, or Executive order.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idec0e1583-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/314/s3">Pub. L. 111–314, § 3</ref>, <date date="2010-12-18">Dec. 18, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3434">124 Stat. 3434</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
